column19: Our shared goal is to apply our combined skills and experience to building an assitive device for muscular dystrophy. We want to develop a prototype we are proud of by sharing the workload and applying class principles to achieve good design quality.
column20: To gain knowledge about how to efficiently and effectively execute a plan to create a rehabilitation device for people with muscle dystrophy. We are currently working to apply the skills and design principles we have learned to be able to create a device we are proud of in the end.
column21: Our shared goal is to create an engineered product we can feel proud of as a final product.
column22: Our shared goal is to collaboratively design and prototype a movement-assistive device that addresses real-world challenges faced by individuals with chronic mobility disorders. We aim to apply our diverse engineering knowledge, co-design effectively, and equally share responsibilities to create a high-quality, user-centered solution that reflects the principles and skills we've learned in class.
column23: Our shared team goal is to apply our skills and experiences to develop a product that targets a specific need, particularly those with muscular dystrophy. Together we plan to become experts in the chosen topic and demonstrate how our prototype benefits those with mobility disabilities.
